    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public static Cigar parse(String cigarString)
        Parse the given Cigar String into a Cigar object. If the cigarString is '*' then this value will return null since there is no alignment information. An invalid cigar string will throw an Exception.
        Parameters:
        cigarString - the cigarString to parse; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a Cigar if the cigar is a valid cigar string that represents a known alignment; null if the cigar string "*".
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if cigarString is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the cigarString is invalild.

      • toGappedTrimmedSequence

        public NucleotideSequence toGappedTrimmedSequence(NucleotideSequence rawUngappedSequence)
        Given this Cigar and the corresponding raw ungapped sequence from the sequencing machine, create the trimmed gapped NucleotideSequence.
        Parameters:
        rawUngappedSequence - the raw ungapped sequence from the sequencing machine; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a NucleotideSequence of the gapped trimmed sequence, will not be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if rawUngappedSequence is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - if rawUngappedSequence has gaps.
        IllegalArgumentException - if rawUngappedSequence ungapped length does not match the cigar unpadded length.

      • toCigarString

        public String toCigarString()
        Convert this Cigar into a formatted "cigar String". The returned cigar string should be valid input into parse(String) such that: 
         Cigar.parse( this.toCigarString() ).equals(this);
        Returns:
        the Cigar as a String using the standard CIGAR format.
